    "Some of the studies Dien et al (2020); Liu et al (2022b); Wang et al (2020); Yang et al (2022) did not provide the model's accuracy even though they used the DNNs technique, which could be the reason behind having this average.",
    "DL models that have been built for predicting student's academic performance require gathering features from the data supplied by students throughout their virtual learning, which can then be analyzed and used for making predictions.",
    "Student's features have been categorized into four groups.",
    "The first category is called demographic features, that include (student's personal, family status, and social data) such as age, gender, health status, occupation, family status, average study hour, and number of friends, etc.",
    "The second category is called previous academic background features such as admission score, type, entrance exams scores, place of previous education, preuniversity subjects, and grades prior to course knowledge, etc."
